[1]
Date: Tue, 16 Mar 2004 11:03:29 -0000
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: ABC Online, Australia [edited]
<http://www.abc.net.au/rural/news/stories/s1066851.htm>

Another outbreak of anthrax in Victoria's Goulburn Valley
-------------------------------------------------
The Department of Primary Industries has confirmed that 8 head of
cattle have died in the past week on neighbouring properties at
Tatura. Surrounding landholders have been informed and advised to
vaccinate their cattle against the fatal disease. Authorities are
confident the outbreak has been contained.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Enquiries were immediately set in motion with the Victoria
veterinary authorities, who replied promptly; see [3]. In the
meanwhile the following report appeared. - Mod.MHJ]
